        "id": 1072905
      },
      "writtenOn": "2026-03-16T16:48:30Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "This condition at L159-160 is saying:\n\n```if this owner had voted on a patch-set in which she owned any file, then we want to copy her vote```\n\nOtherwise \n\n```yes, she had a vote on the prior patch-set, but nothing was owned by her, so the vote should not be copied```.\n\nThis is why (already in the existing code) we are looking at the `[base to previous patchset]` content.\n\nThis new code applies the `auto-owners-approved` at `directory` level, as a way to deactivate the copying of the owners vote for this directory, no matter the previous ownership state.\n\nIf we removed this we would have approvals being sticky even for directories with auto-owners-approval \u003d false`. \n\nLet\u0027s catch up.",
      "parentUuid": "64097812_a2f9d180",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 151,
        "startChar": 0,
        "endLine": 158,
        "endChar": 9
