        "id": 1072905
      },
      "writtenOn": "2026-03-16T16:48:30Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "I don\u0027t think this is the right place to short circuit the filtered result into an an `Optional\u003cMap\u003c\u003e\u003e` or a `null`. This is a filter and it should just filter imho.\n\n- empty set \u003d owns nothing\n- non empty set \u003d owns allowed files\n\n`Null` is effectively representing a third state and I find it awkard that `null` means \"the owner owns at least one file that is banned from auto owners approval\".\n\nI think a `Map` is the right data structure here because the auto-owners-approval policy applies per file, so preserving per file information is the cleanest model imho.\n\nThe short-circuit is a nice idea to stop early, but I suggest we optimise this only if needed.\n\nWDYT?",
